This slide lists some general thoughts on tea tea ess. Note that you need emacs reveal to generate and play audio. This slide uses org properties to specify a break of ten seconds before advancing to the next slide after audio stops. This offers some reading time for the bullet points.
Alternatively, the ess ess em el element break can be used to insert breaks anywhere. The source code of the notes specifies a break of three seconds after this sentence.
<break time="3s" />
Speech then continues with this sentence after those three seconds. Note that break elements are removed from the speaker notes in the presentation as they are meant for software and might confuse readers.
